               <person instant="false"><!--donor-->
                  <persName corresp="PRS0000" instant="false" full="yes">ʾAmdä Śǝllase is mentioned as the commissioner on fol. 129rb, but his name has been written, in vivid red and in a secondary hand, over an erasure. The original owner of the Ms. might be Wäldä ʾAmlak whose name has been retained on fol. 107rb.&#xD;
The name of the commissioner and his family members have been written over erased names in the supplication formulas: ʾAmdä Śǝllase (e.g., fols. 3rac, 6rabc, 7vc, 21va, 26rb, 30vabc, 94rab), his wife Wälättä Haymanot (fols. 90vc, 92rc, 94rab), Ḫǝdrä Mikaʾel (fols. 19rb, 21rc, 21vb, 95va), Gäbrä Śǝllase (fols. 90va, 92rc), Wäldä Śǝllase (Bä-Gäday) (fols. 90vc, 96rb, 99rbc),  ʾƎqwǝba Mikaʾel (fols. 95vb, 104ra). &#xD;
In fols. 3r-90r, the names of Wäldä Mikaʾel (most frequently), Gäbrä Maryam and Sǝḥunä Śǝllase have been added, in black and in another hand, over the names mentioned above.</persName>
